%N A037584 Base 5 digits are, in order, the first n terms of the periodic sequence with initial period 3,1.
%H A037584 <a href="/index/Rec#order_03">Index entries for linear recurrences with constant coefficients</a>, signature (5,1,-5).
%F A037584 G.f.: x*(3+x) / ( (x-1)*(5*x-1)*(1+x) ). - _R. J. Mathar_, Apr 26 2015
%F A037584 a(n) = floor(2*5^n/3). - _Christian Krause_, Jun 07 2026
%F A037584 E.g.f.: exp(-x)*(4*exp(6*x) - 3*exp(2*x) - 1)/6. - _Stefano Spezia_, Jun 07 2026
